---
By: Elbert Hubbard
Locus:
  Page: 452
  Verse: 17
Tags:
  - Suffering
---
The line between failure and success is so fine that we scarcely know when
we pass it： so fine that we are often on the line and don’t know it. How
many a man has thrown up his hands at a time when a little more effort, a
little more patience, would have achieved success.
